---++ Post-2012 Notes

   * OSGPKITransitionCallNotes

---++ 11 Dec 2012

Attending: Von, Mine, Kevin, Anthony, Alain D., Soichi, Chander, Rob, Ruth

Topics:
   * Panda/ATLAS issue (Von)
      * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-249
      * https://ggus.eu/tech/ticket_show.php?ticket=87573
     * There is a fix in gridsite CVS. Not sure what the release cycle is, and then when CERN PANDA would pick it up.
      * AI: Rob to follow up on tomorrow&#39;s OPs call.
      * AI: Von to ping John Hoover.
   * ITB Test coverage (Mine?)
      * Oscar&#39;s comment: &quot;When OSG moves to DigiCert Grid CA1 as the new issuing CA for Host certificates there might be an issue in the SAZ and GUMS client plug-ins. It deserves testing before deployment just to be sure we don&#39;t have the problem there too. I need go through your deployment details and I would like to encourage you to run a test with gLExec and a CE deployment against SAZ and GUMS using DigiCert certificates everywhere.&quot;
      * DigiCert was tested with GUMS and glexec
      * Steve Timm: &quot;we did test SAZ with digicert certificates at the same time we tested GUMS in the testing last fall.  But Mine Altunay has also asked us to do a couple new tests with different proxy configurations that we didn&#39;t consider at that time, and that testing is in progress.  We will also test with our own gridsite installation which is part of FermiCloud to see if we see any problems with that.&quot;
   * Plan for stress-test of system (OIM-ITB) with DigiCert on Dec 19?
   * Update on FNAL service desk issues?


Updates:
   * DigiCert has fixed MPKI Domain Manager access issue
      * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-171
      * Alain and Mine, as registered admins, should be able to access the domain manager in production OSG account.
      * Alain has verified.
      * There is a document on how to do this.
   * DigiCert has implemented two APIs, documentation pending
      * API to access list of registered domains
         * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-9
      * API for status on multiple certificate requests
         * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-272

Notes:
   * Panda/ATLAS issue (Von)
      *https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-249
      * https://ggus.eu/tech/ticket_show.php?ticket=87573
      * There is a fix in gridsite CVS. Not sure what the release cycle is for making an RPM, and then when CERN PANDA would pick it up.
      * This is now an ATLAS issue.
   * Plan for stress-test of system (OIM-ITB) with DigiCert on Dec 19?
      * Will go ahead, pending scheduling with DIgiCert.
   * Update on FNAL service desk issues (Kevin)
      * A couple success stories without re-load (and using IE).
      * ITB was fixed a couple days ago. Production was fixed today.
      * Only issue: did not see any instructions on installing DigiCert root certificate (for Windows).
         * Soichi: happened automatically for him. Kevin: will try third system today and will let Von know if he sees it again.
      * Ruth: Reports of some people getting certificates from OSG PKI, but FNAL policy says they should be waiting for documentation to be in order. This is an issue between FNAL and its RAs.

AI: Von review hisotry on Grid Admin/domain/VO logic
AI: Von to open JIRAs: (1) Grid Admin request should include VO, (2) Route request to GA based on VO of requestor and GA.

---++ 4 Dec 2012

Attending: Von, Mine, Kevin Hill, Alain D., Rob Q., Soichi, Chander, Christiane F. 

Topics:
   * Panda/ATLAS issue (Von)
      * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-249
      * https://ggus.eu/tech/ticket_show.php?ticket=87573
      * There is a fix in gridsite CVS. Not sure what the release cycle is, and then when CERN PANDA would pick it up.
      * AI: Rob to follow up on tomorrow&#39;s OPs call.
      * AI: Von to ping John Hoover.
   * Some host certificate requested being denied: &quot;You are unable to approve this request, as all the domains have not been validated yet.&quot; (Von/Mine)
       * Apparently a configuration problem at DigiCert - domains not validated for &quot;Grid&quot;
       * All domains now validated. Need to test fix.
       * AI: Mine will ask Yujun Wu to re-request certificate. (DONE)
       * We believe this has been resolved. Von has added a note to the Domain page.
   * Seeing strange errors: &quot;null&quot; message in PKCS7 parsing failure (Soichi)
      * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-258
      * Seems to mostly be happening to FusionGrid folks. About half the time. Not clear yet what the issue us. Real diagnosis will need to wait until next week when Soichi is back from Vacation.
      * Please let Von and Soichi know if you see this error.
      * Always starting as guest.
      * Soichi identified likely issue and released patch last week. Haven&#39;t heard anything since then.
      * Christiane did a fair amount of testing and has not seen the issue. Von has not seen any issues in issuance logs.
      * Optimistically calling this resolved.
      * Bug in TomCat 5, but we were using old version. Causes odd failures that weren&#39;t caught by code at expected location, so it resulted in strange error. Will have a much better error message in the future. 

Other business?
   * Kevin: Having issues with a couple people on FNAL service desk with IE only being offered PKCS7 instead of PKCS12.
      * Alain has been working on this: in bringing on Yolanda, ran into a bit of problem, she and someone else were running into a problem with the page &quot;hanging up&quot; then after refresh they only see PKCS7 (w/o private key) and not PKCS12
      * We are aware of one issue with IE. Have a work-around with refreshing the page. Not sure if this is the same issue.
      * Issue is how do they get the private key in PKCS7 file.
      * We think these issues (refesh and lack of PKCS12) are related.
      * What version of IE in use by FNAL? v8.0.17xxx on Windows 7 (v9 is not supported).
      * Folks at FNAL: try renewal at this point.
      * There is already a JIRA about this: https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-221
   * Mine: Other problems with FNAL service desk. Are resolved now. Lesson&#39;s learned?
      * Problems with registering Yolanda. Had contact-only account. Couldn&#39;t associate DN. Alain removed existing account? Tried changing email. Then Alain disabled, then she was able to register. We learned how to disable/enable to clear this issue. Is this an issue with contact-only accounts? Those folks when they register will take over that account. Not sure how we got into a bad state here.
      * Once we finished registering and registered as RA, couldn&#39;t see Approve button. Is resolved now... how did this get fixed? This was related. Take-away is we don&#39;t know how we got into bad state. If this happens again we need to debug. Alain now understands how to fix.
   * Christiane: If certificate isn&#39;t issued, what should user do? If user tries to request a new one, they get an error that the email is already in use. Christiane did the &quot;email+something@domain&quot; trick (this is a hack, not something we want to recommend).
      * Revocation didn&#39;t work.
      * We need to debug this. If it happens again, we should try to catch it.
   * Christiane: If they forget the password before issuance, what should they do? They should cancel the request.
      * How about after issuance? They should revoke and re-request.
      * There is a JIRA for a command-line renewal client. Christiane really like this as it avoids users having to put them into their browser. https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-202





---++ 27 Nov 2012

Call canceled due to travel.

---++ 20 Nov 2012

Informal call due to many folks being gone.

Attending: Von, Rohan, Scott, Anthony, Alain, Chander, Christiane, Mine, John Volmer

Updates from Von:
   * Panda/ATLAS issue
      * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-249
      * https://ggus.eu/tech/ticket_show.php?ticket=87573
      * Fix in GridSite CVS, push still uncertain.
   * Some host certificate requested being denied: &quot;You are unable to approve this request, as all the domains have not been validated yet.&quot;
       * Apparently a configuration problem at DigiCert - domains not validated for &quot;Grid&quot;
       * All domains now validated. Need to test fix.
       * AI: Mine will ask Yujun Wu to re-request certificate.
   * Seeing strange errors: &quot;null&quot; message in PKCS7 parsing failure
      * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-258
      * Seems to mostly be happening to FusionGrid folks. About half the time. Not clear yet what the issue us. Real diagnosis will need to wait until next week when Soichi is back from Vacation.
      * Please let Von and Soichi know if you see this error.
      * Always starting as guest.
   * Documentation now available: https://www.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Security/PKIDocumentationIndex
      * Report any gaps or errors please.
   * DigiCert audit test
      * Von met with DigiCert last week. Laid foundation for test audit. Expect guidance from DigiCert in early December.

Other topics?
   * Host request process (Anthony)
      * Re Yujun requested host certificate for LQCD, at FNAL but Anthony not authoritative (he is CMS). He is seeing host requests for every experiment at FNAL since we email by domain and not VO. 
      * AI: Von: OIM knows VO of requestor and GA, can it only notify GAs for VO in question?
   * Christiane: Users cannot reapply is request fails because email is already in use.
   * When we will request RAs be signing up for VOs?
      * FNAL RAs have not signed up yet. We don&#39;t know why?
      * AI: Von to check with John Benson as to why.
      * People requesting user certs from OSG VO because they don&#39;t know where else to go - their VO was not available. If they can provide with Sponsor, Alain will go ahead and process it. Some can provide and some cannot.
      * Our correct response is: If they can provide a sponsor we will issue them a cert, otherwise their VO is not registered and we cannot serve them and they should go talk to their VO about this.
   * Christiane: User&#39;s need to import into browsers. This will be a problem if they get a new computer.

---++ 13 Nov 2012

Canceled due to SC12 and meeting in Santa Cruz.

---++ 6 Nov 2012

Canceled due to travel.

---++ 30 Oct 2012

Attending: Jim, Von, Ruth, Rob

*Action Items:*
   * AI: Von to capture - need to educate VOs that when they change their VOMS DN (DONE)
   * AI: Alain to update RA processes to capture: We want to encourage Sponsors to have an OIM account, if they don&#39;t the onus is on the RA to capture the sponsor&#39;s contact information.
   * AI: Rob is writing a twiki document on vomses file change: https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Operations/VomsesFilewithNewPKI (Want review of VOMS certificate expiring by Tim)

New Action Items:
   * AI: Von to raise Brian&#39;s fix with Maarten, include Rob to raise at WLCG Operations meeting.
   * AI: Jim to open ticket - Identify what in ATLAS workflow is adding certificates to proxies (email GOC)
   * AI: Ruth will open request regarding Panda server for testing.[DONE]
   * AI: Rob to raise this issue with WLG Ops call.
   * AI: Rob to open OIM ticket to add checkbox to registration form that indicates intention to use PKI at present. This removes need for support center and presentation to Ops WG.
   * AI: Von to update https://www.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Security/OSGCATransition2012

*Agenda:*

Report out on RA and Grid Admin training from prior week
   * Went well. Everyone was able to do everything, no problems with command-line tools. Very few had to use test domain.
   * Next steps on training
      * Von and Ruth will iterate once on list of those missing and Ruth will email, pointing them at recorded.

Current command-line client RPM (1.0.4) OK for next OSG software release?
   * Any issues from GA training on Friday?
   * No, let&#39;s ship 1.0.4 RPM in next software release.

Update on ATLAS/Panda issue:
   * https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-249
   * We think Brian has a fix for GridSite, has pushed into OSG RPM repository, so it will accept CA certificates in proxy file.
   * We really need this pushed to the Panda server at CERN, John H. is the only one able to update GGUS certificate.
   * OpenSSL has different logic paths if CA certs come from client as opposed to trust root.
   * It seems to be a combination of CA certificates in proxy file and pathlen=0.
   * Next steps?
   * Either push fixes to CERN or try and replicate ourselves. Brian has put up gridsite server and tested his fix.
   * AI: Von to raise Brian&#39;s fix with Martin, include Rob to raise at WLCG Operations meeting.
   * AI: Jim to open ticket - Identify what in ATLAS workflow is adding certificates to proxies (email GOC)
   * AI: Ruth will open request regarding Panda server for testing.
   * AI: Rob to raise this issue with WLG Ops call.

Documentation assignments
   * https://www.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Security/PKIDocumentationIndex
   * Mainly to Mine, Von, Alain - Von will email them to make sure they are aware.
   * Goal is completion by Nov 9.

Discussion on registration of &quot;PKI-only&quot; VOs and enrollment process
   * Need special case in OIM that are joining to use certificates. PNNL and Argonne just went through current process
   * DayaBay may be a similar case.
   * AI: Rob to open OIM ticket to add checkbox to registration form that indicates intention to use PKI at present. This removes need for support center and presentation to Ops WG.

Discussion about what happens with this call after Feb 1, 2013
   * Continue holding this call, or roll it into existing Monday Operations call.

Other:
   * Jim&#39;s last day with OSG is tomorrow Oct 31.
   * Jim main role has been training, other issue he is involved is the Panda issue.   

---++ 23 Oct 2012

Attending: Jim B., Mine, Chander, Rob Q., Von, John H., Anthony, Soichi, Suchandra

Action Items:
   * AI: Von to capture - need to educate VOs that when they change their VOMS DN. (Captured in Documentation twiki page)
   * AI: Alain to update RA processes to capture: We want to encourage Sponsors to have an OIM account, if they don&#39;t the onus is on the RA to capture the sponsor&#39;s contact information.
   * AI: Rob is writing a twiki document on vomses file change: https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Operations/VomsesFilewithNewPKI
   * AI: Jim to see where John H. is on DN transition testing. Can Transition testing be closed out. (DONE - see PANDA issue)
   * AI: Chander to review operations impact document. If he is happy, this is done. (DONE by end of call)

Ongoing tasks:
   * Project Management (Von)
      * New document: https://www.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Security/PKIDocumentationIndex
         * Mine suggests this as top priority.
      * New document: https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Operations/PKITransitionPlan
   * Web UI Development/Deployment (Soichi)
      * 60-seconds is a ceiling.
      * Can we start implementing a performance tracking?
      * Skipped OIM release this week - next release is Nov 13. (This is SC but I think that is OK.)
   * CLI tool development/packaging (Rohan/Von/Tim C./Mat S.): https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/SOFTWARE-758
      * Von is working on plan for 1.1 release and transition to OSG SW team.
   * Training (Mine/Jim): https://opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Security/DigiCertTrainingPlan
      * Report out on 10/22 RA Training - fine, only real issue was Indigo outage. 15 RAs training. No showstoppers. DN mapping to pool accounts for CMS, everyone agreed CMS seems to have a good handle. Couple of FNAL service desk managers had to take it later in the afternoon (Jim gave it twice).
      * Status on GA enrollment? Have 30 people registered. (Alain is out ill.)
      * AI: Jim will provide diff - what RAAs are not trained.

   * Update on DN transition testing (Jim/Anthony/John)
      * PANDA/ATLAS issue: https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-249
      * John Hoover - a curl command is failing from ATLAS pilot; but when manually run from a BNL worker node; very strange as we think environment is the same.
      * Problem: executing from pilot, connecting to PANDA server, Apache + mod_gridsite; job dispatch step - pilot asks server for job payload; over https, called from pilot using curl; appears to be failing when run from Pilot using DigiCert proxy in batch mode
      * Seems to work OK with DOE Grids-derived proxy but error seems to occur with DigiCert-derived proxy 
      * This is w/o glexec, pilot is running as John
      * Theory: DigiCert proxy with additional layer of delegation from Condor-G is rejected by gridsite?
      * PANDA does a curl callback? No, always from WN to PANDA @ CERN.
      * Mine: We have a test PANDA server in ITB, why didn&#39;t we see the problem there? John doesn&#39;t think so. There is only one PANDA server in the world.
      * AI: Mine to check with Suchandra on how much ITB tested DigiCert with PANDA. DONE: Suchandra says we was using ATLAS PANDA system, but we didn&#39;t do DigiCert testing.
      * PANDA at CERN presumably uses a CERN CA-issued host certificate.
      * Suchandra: Does not have APS pilot set up. That means no ATLAS pilots were submitted with DigiCert certificate in ITB.
      * ITB doesn&#39;t have a service up and running to test DigiCert certificates with PANDA. 
      * AI: Suchandra will try ....something details of which I missed... to compare DOE Grids PKI and DigiCert.
      * GridSite has a history of sensitivity to parameters in certificate chains.

 

