Notes:
   * Working through this https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/twiki/pub/Operations/DigiCertPlanningDevAndImplementation/OSG-PKI-Acceptance-Criteria-2.docx
   * Just focusing OIM, will do with client tools later
   * Section 2, MUSTS:
      1 All GOC software is Apache v2
         * Should make sure this is stated somewhere in the source code.
         * Goal here is that OSG has access to software if IU leaves consortium
      2 Version scheme: protocol has a version
      3 Test suite: Have a few unit tests, not comprehensive. Access control requirements makes testing hard. Most testing is &#39;friendly user&#39; testing.
         * Have a testing period on ITB is acceptable.
      4 End-user documentation: in the case of OIM this is the web pages itself
      5 Internal developer documentation:
         * This is a bigger concern, how would a second developer come up to speed? How is it build and deployed?
         * Alex D. has been added to OIM development
         * We have: https://docs.google.com/a/vonwelch.com/document/d/1-noGy__JKaXP218k3jxtlbl--iuOUCNarL5vBDbxbSk/edit#
         * Result: some work need to be done here to document built processes.
      6 Source code repository with versioning scheme: use subversion, branch every release
      7 External code review:
         * This is more applicable to CLI, since SW team will be taking this over.
         * We don&#39;t have expertise to do this for OIM (javascript, other web technologies) on OSG SW team.
         * Should we do webapp testing for OIM? We should at least do low-hanging fruit. OWASP.
         * MIST is an option, but would need to be resourced.
         * What about GUMS, VOMRS developers? Doesn&#39;t seem likely they have spare cycles.
         * Alain is fine with state of affairs here for OIM.
      * With exception of completing documentation for item 5, Alain is happy with section 2.
   * Section 2, SHOULDS:
      1 Use community software: Not applicable.
      2 Widely-known technologies: Acceptable
      3 See 5 above.
      4 See 7 above.
   * Section 3:
      * These items are pending, have ITB testing coming up.
   *  Section 4:
      * 4.1: Approval: DONE
      * 4.2: Auditing: This is all in OIM logs, via OIM-log interface. 
         * AI: Soichi will send Von URL and screen shots of logs for approval.
      * 4.3: General format: DigiCert is generating certificates.
      * 4.4: DN form: DigiCert is responsible for forming the DN
         * AI: We should check DNs and alert GOC staff if we see something unexpected (but not error out).
      * 4.5: Certificate Lifetime: DigiCert sets this
         * AI: Augment above AI, we should check lifetime
   * Section 5:
      * 5.1.1: Integrity of Auditing: All OIM DB content is backed up to back up server, daily snaps shots for 60 days, backup server is backed up to tape.
         * AI: Is there off-site (non-Bton data center) backup?
      * 5.1.2: Protection from modification: is protected by usual mysql access controls and unix file system permissions. Access limited to GOC staff and limited by bastion host. Back ups provide extra protection.
      * 5.1.3: Any changes to auditing will be logged: no applicable, all database changes are logged.
      * 5.1.4: Any attempt to modify logs will be logged:  all database changes are logged.
      * 5.1.5: Time sycnhronizing: Run NTP, and monitor against 2nd second system to sanity check.
      * 5.2.1: Unexpected errors will be logged: Yes, are are forward to GOC service alert.
      * 5.2.2: Any violation of policy: We don&#39;t allow violations of policy, see PKI System Design Doc.
   * Section 6: Authentication
      * 6.1: Failed authentication attempts will be logged: We do certificate-based authentication, handled by Apache. Apache logs failures. We don&#39;t currently monitor.
      * 6.2: Trusted Agents shall be authenticated with valid DigiCert certificate: TA must authenticate. We currently accept any IGTF certificate for OIM. We don&#39;t currently enforce the use of a specific CA for TA.
         * TA role is bound to contact Id, one can map multiple certificates contact ID. We could implement TA as an authorization and force binding to a DN.
         * AI: Do we need to limit Trusted Agents to use of DigiCert certificates?
         * AI: Under the old system, reach TA/GA had to renew their rights each year with certificate renewal. Was this purposeful?
   * Section 7:
      * We don&#39;t currently have a defined process for this for the OSG CA. Should define a process where all of this is logged as a ticket, which becomes the audit record.
      * AI: Define this process.
   * Section 8:
      * 8.1.1: We have 3 limits - global for the entire OSG for year, user has an annual limit (3 user certificates, 1000 host certificates) , user has a daily limit for host certificates (50); these are administratively adjustable.
      * 8.1.2: Track and notify when certain levels are reached:
         * Have Munin plug-in to monitor number of requests: https://internal.grid.iu.edu/munin/ITB_VMs/oim-itb/cert_quota.html URL here.
         * 75% of threshold, 85% is critical and sends warnings on these levels.
         * Multiple thresholds are problematic.
         * AI: Change warning to 50%, critical to 75%.
      * 8.1.3: No longer a requirement. See https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/OSGPKI-69
      * 8.1.4: See 8.1.1
      * 8.1.5: See 8.1.1
      * 8.2.1: Host Certificate Approvers of host certificates shall be Grid Admins: Implemented
      * 8.2.2: GA shall be restricted to a domain: Confirmed
      * 8.3.1: User email addresses must be in DigiCert.
         * AI: Need to add checking of user&#39;s email domain.
      * 9.1: Private key generation logging: Von will verify this when he verifies logging for item 5.
         * This is not explicit, private key is created when certificate generated, and when session expires.
         * Want to be able to answer question: what keys were on the system during a given time frame?
         * Private key deletion is tied to session expiration - is this logged? Not currently, but can be turned on.
         * AI: Private key deletion should be implicitly or explicitly logged? Can we overwrite private key with noise? Or are we at mercy of GC?
      * 9.2: Private keys encrypted with strength-tested pass phrase: Done.
      * Section 10: Host certificate revocation works today, user certificate revocation is pending support from DigiCert.
      * Section 11: Training and Testing:
         * We have this with OIM ITB.

  
